WEBVTT



00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:15.200
Met a person named Judas.

00:00:15.584 --> 00:00:21.024
Never heard of a pregnant mother mulling that name over for her expectant child.

00:00:21.408 --> 00:00:25.088
Judas is a name that has been permanently stained.

00:00:25.376 --> 00:00:27.328
He's the obvious villain.

00:00:27.584 --> 00:00:33.856
Slipped away from the original communion table to sell out the one breaking the bread and pouring the wine. How could he?

00:00:34.304 --> 00:00:37.024
After all these seen, all these heard,

00:00:37.376 --> 00:00:47.424
What misconception must he have carried silently all these years? What seething resentment must he have fostered? What moment did he feel so forgotten, so?

00:00:46.944 --> 00:00:54.592
Oh, excluded, so unloved that it had come to this. What lie had the deceiver contorted in his imagination? Amen.

00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:57.760
Until it grew into distrust, this demonstrable.

00:00:58.496 --> 00:01:03.552
When Judas abruptly left in the middle of the meal, they assumed he'd gone out to.

00:01:03.328 --> 00:01:06.176
Make an offering to the poor, after all.

00:01:06.048 --> 00:01:09.728
He was the treasurer, he'd always run the books, and.

00:01:09.664 --> 00:01:19.712
On the first night of Passover, its tradition to make an offering to the poor. it made sense he'd go to give to make sure that all the rituals were observed. in reality,

00:01:19.232 --> 00:01:20.288
Reality. Reality.

00:01:20.320 --> 00:01:27.808
He went out to collect money for the life of the rabbi, the life of the savior, the king of kings, disguised in peasant rags.

00:01:27.968 --> 00:01:30.464
Sold for a handful of shekels.

00:01:30.976 --> 00:01:35.552
Judas may be the obvious villain, but he is certainly not the only villain.

00:01:36.736 --> 00:01:38.816
Couldn't you stay awake with me?

00:01:39.456 --> 00:01:41.152
Even for an hour?

00:01:42.272 --> 00:01:43.744
In English

00:01:43.872 --> 00:01:46.752
Present speaks so much louder than words.

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:51.744
when we are grieving hurting dreading the presence of a friend

00:01:51.872 --> 00:01:55.616
Speaks louder than the most eloquent consolation.

00:01:55.808 --> 00:01:57.408
And it was just that.

00:01:57.632 --> 00:01:59.776
The presence of a friend.

00:02:00.160 --> 00:02:01.792
That Jesus lacked

00:02:02.240 --> 00:02:05.696
When Jesus prayed for the strength to surrender his will,

00:02:05.376 --> 00:02:12.704
Peter sharpened a sword for the assumed battle. John snooze. James's distracted mind wandered. not a single one of them.

00:02:13.120 --> 00:02:14.944
Not a single one of us.

00:02:15.328 --> 00:02:19.200
Able to remain present to the God who is ever present.

00:02:19.040 --> 00:02:20.256
To us.

00:02:20.544 --> 00:02:29.376
If the parable of the prodigal son had taught them nothing else, surely they remembered this much that it is just as possible to betray the father from.

00:02:29.216 --> 00:02:32.640
His own house as it is to run off to the pigsty.

00:02:33.536 --> 00:02:35.776
Couldn't you keep watch with me?

00:02:36.384 --> 00:02:38.016
Even for an hour.

00:02:38.816 --> 00:02:44.896
How many times did that brief exchange replay in Peter's imagination in the next 72 hours?

00:02:44.864 --> 00:02:51.232
how many times did james or john wish they could go back and kneel there next to him in the garden but they couldn't.

00:02:51.360 --> 00:02:52.928
They betrayed him.

00:02:53.312 --> 00:02:54.976
However quietly,

00:02:55.744 --> 00:03:00.672
Within 24 hours, they'd all been the one to dip the bread in the bowl.

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:07.200
All betrayed him in one way or another, all sold him for the currency of their own honour, comfort, convenience.

00:03:06.944 --> 00:03:13.376
All disgraced the name at which every knee will bow to keep their own names unstained.

00:03:13.632 --> 00:03:15.488
And we've all followed suit.

00:03:16.256 --> 00:03:22.400
All dipped our own hands into the bowl of betrayal, all stained his name to keep ours clean.

00:03:22.976 --> 00:03:25.088
In the words of Frederick Buechner,

00:03:25.184 --> 00:03:30.016
Judas is only the first in a procession of betrayers two thousand years long.

00:03:30.336 --> 00:03:36.608
If Jesus were to exclude him from his love and forgiveness to one degree or another, he would have to exclude us all.

00:03:37.504 --> 00:03:44.032
At the very table that Judas tipped his hand by dipping it under the bowl of Jesus offered his life.

00:03:43.744 --> 00:03:50.464
Has broken bread, his blood has shared wine for all of his loud and quiet betrayers.

00:03:50.624 --> 00:03:54.080
No matter how dramatic or subtle our offences.

00:03:54.400 --> 00:04:03.936
a table that jesus told his followers to pass on from generation to generation to remember remember what we're all so prone to forget

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:06.752
That it's his costly forgiveness

00:04:06.848 --> 00:04:09.440
Not my squeaky cleanness.

00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:11.264
That makes me fit.

00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:13.888
To sit and feast forever at his table.

00:04:14.624 --> 00:04:15.840
tonight

00:04:15.616 --> 00:04:19.552
You have not come to reflect on an old story, but a current one.

00:04:19.488 --> 00:04:22.144
a story you are very much living in.

00:04:22.272 --> 00:04:26.208
A story you are invited before we read another word of it.

00:04:26.368 --> 00:04:28.864
To become a participant within.

00:04:29.600 --> 00:04:39.648
All among us who are honest enough to admit that they too are in that long procession of betrayers behind Judas, all willing to say, I too have dipped my hand in.

00:04:39.168 --> 00:04:41.120
Hand in the bowl of betrayal.

00:04:40.960 --> 00:04:44.288
Our invite is come now to Jesus' table.

00:04:44.544 --> 00:04:47.104
Where you will instead dip your hand

00:04:46.976 --> 00:04:48.352
and a cup.

00:04:48.192 --> 00:04:49.696
Of forgiveness.

00:04:49.728 --> 00:04:50.624
Thank you
